  "prompt": "What should I do to make my crush notice me?",
  "response": "Making your crush notice you can be a delicate task, but there are several thoughtful strategies you could try:\n\n1. **Be Yourself**: Confidence and authenticity are attractive. Show your true self and don\u2019t try to be someone you\u2019re not.\n\n2. **Show Interest**: Engage in conversations, ask questions about their interests, and listen actively. Showing genuine interest in what they say will make a positive impression.\n\n3. **Common Interests**: Find common interests or hobbies that you both enjoy. This can give you more opportunities to spend time together and bond over shared activities.\n\n4. **Be Positive**: Positivity and a good sense of humor can be really attractive qualities. Try to maintain a positive attitude and positivity will likely draw people towards you.\n\n5. **Be Adaptable**: Sometimes being flexible and open to new experiences makes you more approachable. Show willingness to try new things and be open-minded.\n\n6. **Improve Yourself**: Focus on personal growth and self-improvement. Whether it\u2019s learning new skills, pursuing your passions, or maintaining healthy habits, self-improvement can make you more attractive.\n\n7. **Friends First**: Sometimes building a friendship first can naturally lead to romantic interest. Get to know them on a friendly level without pressure.\n\n8. **Be Social**: Spend time in social settings where your crush is likely to be. Don\u2019t isolate yourself, but rather participate in group activities and events.\n\n9. **Use Body Language**: Positive body language can indicate that you are interested. Smile, maintain eye contact, and use open gestures.\n\n10. **Compliment Them**: Genuine, sincere compliments can go a long way. Make sure they are thoughtful and not overdone.\n\nRemember, while effort is important, it\u2019s also key to respect their feelings and boundaries. If they don\u2019t seem interested, it\u2019s important to gracefully accept it and move on.",
